# Green Office 2026 Governance Rules

## Constitution-First
Always reference 00-GREENOFFICE_PROJECT_CONSTITUTION.MD before making decisions.

## GitHub is Source of Truth
All project assets originate from GitHub. No direct production editing.

## Static-First Principle
Prefer Markdown → JSON → CSV before considering database/API/backend.

## Reuse Before Generate
Check existing components, documents, templates, and assets before creating new ones.

## Context Pack Before Long Prompt
Use curated context packs for agent tasks. Avoid large prompt dumps.

## Chunk Not Dump
Large files must be chunked, indexed, and retrieved - never pasted directly into AI.

## Markdown First
Knowledge must be stored in Markdown for token efficiency.

## No Database/API/Backend (MVP)
Do not add database, API, or backend services unless approved by Product Owner.

## No Production Edit
Direct production editing is strictly prohibited.

## Build PASS ≠ Release Ready
Runtime QA is required before declaring completion.

## Token-Saving Workflow
Reuse → Context Pack → Chunk → Skill → Build → QA → Commit

## RTK Policy (Local Agent Helper)
- Prefer RTK for repeated shell operations (`rtk git status`, `rtk npm run build`, `rtk ls`, `rtk read`)
- Record reusable RTK commands in `docs/runbooks/RTK_USAGE.md` when patterns emerge
- Use `rtk gain` periodically to review token savings
- Do **not** use RTK to edit or deploy to production — RTK only compresses command output
- Use direct `npm` / `git` binaries when the RTK PowerShell wrapper blocks native behavior (e.g. `npm install`)
- See skill **RTK_WORKFLOW** in `docs/KB/SKILLS_REGISTRY.md`